Q1. What is NX Monorepo and how does it support micro-frontend architecture in Angular applications? Can you describe how you would structure multiple Angular apps and libraries using NX?
Q2. What are the different ways components can communicate in Angular? How would you handle communication between two Angular micro frontends built using NX?
Q3. A complex Angular application with multiple micro frontends is experiencing performance lags in production. What tools and techniques would you use to debug and optimize it?
Q4. How would you set up a unit testing strategy in an NX monorepo Angular project using Jest or Mocha? What are the benefits of following Test Driven Development (TDD) in frontend development?
Q5. You are leading a frontend team working on multiple Angular micro frontends. How would you ensure code quality, team alignment, and smooth CI/CD delivery across modules?
